PIMS Group offers a broad range of technical expertise, project management, operational and statutory support for the coal mining and related industries. With more than 100 years of combined experience in the mining industry, our team has significant depth of skills and experience, enabling our clients to deliver operational goals, targets and projects on time and within budget.

PIMS Group partners with clients nationally and internationally to deliver value realisation by addressing their current and future business needs, ensuring they meet stakeholder expectations and operational requirements in conjunction with statutory obligations.

PIMS Group specifically focuses on underground and surface coal mining nationally and internationally, enabling the embedding of best practice within each project regardless of its size.

Our Services

PIMS Group has seven distinct business units that work independently and in conjunction with each other, to deliver cost-effective and value-based solutions for all stages of a coal mining project. Whether you are looking for technical expertise, project management, operational & statutory support, or training solutions, PIMS Group is your partner of choice.


Mining Solutions

With over 100 years of combined experience in the mining industry, our team have extensive knowledge and skills, offering innovative solutions for specific projects and every day operational issues.
PIMS Consulting – Technical expertise & project management for any stage of mining operations;
PIMS Mining – Operational & trades personnel for production, maintenance & support activities;
PIMS Training – Delivery of nationally accredited training and statutory mentoring;
PIMS Engineering - Maintenance & overhaul of machinery/equip & general fabrication at our Moranbah Workshop;
Real Time Strata Monitoring – A real-time roof convergence monitoring system, for early detection of strata movement;
Equipment Hire – Extensive fleet of mining equipment for both long & short term hire;
Safety Management - We can help improve your safety, health and risk management systems;
